definition:
παρ-ἐρχομαι 
 [in LXX chiefly for עָבַר ;] 
  1. to pass, pass by; 
   (a) of persons: absol., Luk.18:37; with accusative of person(s), Mrk.6:48; with accusative lot., Act.16:8; before διά, with genitive, Mat.8:28; 
   (b) of things : τ. ποτήριον, Mat.26:39 (ἀπ᾽ ἐμοῦ), Mat.26:42; of time, Mat.14:15, Mrk.14:35, Act.27:9, 1Pe.4:3. Metaphorical, 
   (a) to pass away, perish: Mat.5:18 24:34-35 Mrk.13:30-31, Luk.16:17 21:32-33, 2Co.5:17, Jas.1:10, 2Pe.3:10; 
   (b) to pass by, neglect, disregard: with accusative of thing(s), Luk.11:42 15:29. 
   2. to come to, arrive: Luk.12:37 17:7, Act.24:7, R, mg. (cf. ἀντι-παρέρχομαι).†
 SYN.: παραβαίνω  (AS)
